# lld --symbol-ordering-file
#
# Hot-startup symbol order for `bun <file>` / `bun .` / `bun run <script>` /
# `bun -p` / `bun --version`. lld clusters the symbols listed here at the front
# of their output section (`.text`, `.rodata`), packing the cold-start working
# set into one contiguous run of pages instead of letting fat-LTO scatter it
# across the ~50 MB `.text` blob (Rust CGUs + WebKit/JSC/ICU land in arbitrary
# order, so hot bring-up code otherwise shares 64 KB fault-around windows with
# cold bun_install / bun_bundler / bun_css / unused-ICU bodies).
#
# THIS LIST IS PROFILE-GENERATED, not hand-authored. It is the union of the
# `.text` symbols touched (in any call-stack frame) during cold start across
# the `bun -p`, `bun .`, `bun <file>`, `bun run`, `require("fs")` and
# `--version` paths, ordered by first-touch time. Regenerate when the boot
# path changes (B=build/<profile>/bun-profile):
#   for p in '-p 1+1' '.' empty.js req-fs.js --version 'run noop'; do
#     perf record -F4000 -e cycles:u -g -o "$p.data" -- bash -c "for i in {1..80}; do \$B $p >/dev/null 2>&1; done"
#   done
#   # then, per .data: perf script, and for each sample walk its stack
#   # root->leaf keeping first-seen symbols from the bun-profile DSO; concat
#   # the files in priority order; dedup; that ordered list is this file.
#
# Single-pass, best-effort: lld silently drops entries it can't resolve
# (paired with -Wl,--no-warn-symbol-ordering in scripts/build/flags.ts), so the
# Rust v0 `Cs<hash>_` disambiguators / post-LTO `.llvm.<N>` / `.<N>` suffixes
# baked in here just lose a little clustering when stale and cost zero extra
# link time (no 2-pass relink). Over-listing is free.
#
# The `.llvm.<N>` LTO-internalization suffixes change *every build*, so a stale
# one silently un-clusters that hot fn (its first call then faults a ~64 KB
# window of cold neighbours into RSS). Refresh them against a fresh linker map
# whenever they drift — `--profile=btg` writes build/btg/bun-profile.linker-map:
#   bun run startup-order:sync            # dry run: show drift
#   bun run startup-order:sync -- --write # rewrite this file; commit the diff
# (`bun run startup-order:sync -- --check` is the CI guard.)
#
# Linux release only (see flags.ts).

# ── .init_array / libc / mimalloc init (run before perf's first sample) ──
_start
frame_dummy
__cpu_indicator_init
register_tm_clones
_GLOBAL__sub_I_eh_alloc.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I.00090_globals_io.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I_cxx11_locale_inst.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I_cxx11_wlocale_inst.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I_locale_inst.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I_system_error.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I_ios_errcat.cc
_ZL17mi_process_attachv
_ZL20mi_process_init_oncev
_ZL18mi_heap_init_theapPK9mi_heap_s
mi_thread_init

