# ── hot read-only data: default-command clap arg-parse tables ──
# Only the tables `bun <file>` / `bun .` / `bun --version` actually deref:
# AUTO_TABLE (`comptime_table!` → `.rodata.startup`, already front-of-`.rodata`
# via the section name; listed here for completeness) and the
# BASE_RUNTIME_TRANSPILER fallback. RUN_TABLE / BUILD_TABLE / TEST_TABLE are
# `comptime_table!(.., cold)` (plain `.rodata`) and deliberately *not* listed
# here — the `--version` fault-around window faults this run on every start, so
# tables only `bun run` / `bun build` / `bun test` touch are dead weight on it.
# RUN_TABLE (the `bun run` arg-parse table) is left to LTO crate-order placement
# inside `bun_runtime`'s rodata, next to the npm-script dispatch code it shares
# a working set with — pulling it to the front of `.rodata` would only separate
# it from those neighbours.
